# Shell scripts must stay LF — Windows checkouts with core.autocrlf=true
# otherwise convert them to CRLF, which breaks when a script like
# backend/docker-entrypoint.sh is bind-mounted into a Linux container and
# run via `sh`: `sh` reads the trailing \r as part of the option string
# (e.g. `set -eu\r`) and fails with "Illegal option -".
*.sh text eol=lf
